rdeners will make new connections and discoveries in a way standard alphabetical lists simply don’t allow. Alternately, gardeners who want to look up a particular term can jump right into the alphabetical index. Each entry includes the different forms of the term, a basic pronunciation guide, the definition, and an example plant species. Rich botanical illustrations make this guide as beautiful as it is useful, while a durable flexi-bound cover means the book can withstand both days in the garden and evenings on the nightstand.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aBotanyvTerminology. 0aLatin languagevDictionariesxEnglish. 7aGARDENING / General.2bisacsh  alatin, language, botany, botanists, garden, gardeners, gardening, plants, planting, names, naming, meaning, royal horticultural society, horticulture, botanical, flowers, color, leaves, form, habitat, scent, taste, time, pronunciation guide, definition, explanation, species, terminology, terms, dictionary, understanding, background information, features, comparisons, associations.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311071193640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226455532423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226455532/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles